Reports incorrect usages of transition table variables in triggers.
<p>Example (HSQLDB):</p>
<pre><code>CREATE TABLE foo(a INT);

CREATE TRIGGER trg
 AFTER DELETE ON foo
BEGIN
   SELECT * FROM NEW;
END;

CREATE TRIGGER trig AFTER INSERT ON foo
   REFERENCING OLD ROW AS newrow
   FOR EACH ROW WHEN (a > 1)
   INSERT INTO foo VALUES (1)</code></pre>
<p>In HSQLDB, DELETE triggers may be used only with the OLD state while INSERT triggers may have only the NEW state. So, in the previous
  example, NEW in <code>SELECT * FROM NEW;</code> will be highlighted as well as OLD in <code>REFERENCING OLD ROW AS newrow</code>.</p>
